@SP that's almost right. A genome is an individual organism's entire genetic material-- even though it can be used more loosely as in the human genome project, it doesn't typically refer to a species level property. So clones would share a genome.

Genotype is used to refer to an individual organism's version of a specific genetic sequence-- not to the whole genome. Clones would also share all the same genotypes.

Then gene set, as you say, is a collection of genes related by function. Which clones would have in common, because each gene set is a subset of their identical genomes.

